<br>
- Blades 50 is better than CD 50 because it gives you a maxed weapskill. That leads to better damage, higher to hit chance and more style bonus with blades styles.<br>
<br>
- I am Blades 50 myself and I use CD styles only when there is no blade style covering it, i.e. Parry and Evade Chains. I respecced to Blades 50, Parry 42, CD 39 after having the balanced 44/44/44 for quite some time. After respec I hit harder and more often and did not notice a huge decrease in off hand swings.<br>
<br>
- The Fire Blade/Spectrum Blade Combo is better than Hurricane Solar Flare.<br>
<br>
Hurricane has a Med Defense Penalty while Fire Blade has only a low one. From all the tests I read Defense modifiers make a difference.<br>
<br>
The Follow Up, Spectrum Blade has a Medium Defense Bonus, Solar Flare only a low one.<br>
<br>
Hurricane/Solar Flare has no effect, Fire Blade/Spectrum Blade has an attack speed debuff on the follow up style.<br>
<br>
So, the CD anytime style has no benefit. The Blades styles are better in any single way.<br>
<br>
- Behind Style chains WOULD look better in CD IF the snare wasn't broken.<br>
<br>
Of course he is so there is no reason using Snow Shower/Gale (or Ice Storm)<br>
<br>
So, the Revenging Blade/Brilliant Blade is better (for me with Blades 50) than Snow Shower/Gale;Ice Storm.<br>
<br>
- About using two weapons of same speed, I can't really help you. I use bastard sword/crescent sword atm until I ding rr5.<br>
<br>
From the tests I did, I have a slightly better dps atm with the bastard sword (which is 99%) in main hand than the crescent sword (100%) - all other stats, skills etc unchanged.<br>
<br>
I use it because I like the look of it and don't see a disadvantage. And after reading that there is a bug with dps 16.5 weapons having a higher damage variance until you hit rr5, I will continue to use it.<br>
<br>
The only reason I can imagine to use a slow and a fast weapon other than that could be the flipped coin issue. If I got it right, the engine flips a coind to determine with which speed you swing your weapons. It either uses off hand speed or main hand speed.<br>
<br>
That means, when you use bastard sword/short sword combo, you would either swing again after 4.1 or 2.4 seconds.<br>
<br>
If you have the same speed weapons, 2 sickles for example, you would continuously swing every 2.9 secs.<br>
<br>
Hope it helps (this time)<br>
